organic_results.title: Inputs, outputs, and the prestige of university science departments
organic_results.snippet: This paper reports correlates of departmental prestige (American Council on Education ratings of the quality of graduate faculty, 1966) for a sample of 125 departments in mathematics, physics, chemistry, and biology. The analysis mostly uses multivariate linear regression. Large and significant correlations with departmental prestige exist for measures of department size, research production, research opportunities, faculty background (including quality of Ph.
